address: 2-6 E 2nd St, Jamestown, NY 14701, United States

analyzed_reviews.review:
This was our first time visiting. We went up for our wedding anniversary. The food tasted amazing. I had the loin with mashed potatoes and asparagus. My wife had the shrimp special. I also indulged on an 8oz glass of cabernet. Being our anniversary, they gifted us a well plated, lava cake, with a card signed by the staff!

The service was also great. Our waiter, Jesse/Jessie (not sure of the spelling) was very personable and knowledgeable. He checked in on us an appropriate amount of times as well. At one point, one manager asked us about our evening, which was nice.

The atmosphere is more modern with dim lit features and nice light fixtures. A couple of things that got me a bit would be the older tables that are just covered and some finishing work not being done around corners and lights. Being a fairly high-priced place to eat in the area, it also seemed weird that people in street clothes and ball caps were coming in for the bar.

Overall my wife and I had a great dinner and enjoyed ourselves. We will be back and urge you to visit!

address: 109 George St, Hamilton, ON L8P 1E3, Canada

analyzed_reviews.review:
I went here for dinner with a friend on a weekday evening. I ordered the Amigos Famous Wrap Cruncho Supremo and it was delicious! I like that it came with chips and salsa. The portion size was pretty good for the price too.

Our server was great as well. She was very friendly and helpful.

The overall atmosphere was cool with the lights hanging from the ceiling. We didn’t sit outside on the patio but it appeared to have an equally cool vibe to it.

With a very colorful exterior and a well furnished interior, once you walk in you're hit with the loud music and chatter. If you're looking for a place to have a quiet dinner this is not the place as it's just bursting with energy.

We were immediately seated with the lovely staff. If you take a look around you can see the kitchen and the cooks working right in front of you which is a nice touch.

We ordered the loaded nachos as an appetizer  and the birria tacos, enchiladas, and quesadillas as our entree.

I feel 20 dollars for nachos is a bit steep but everything else was reasonably priced.

The food was great but I wouldn't call it the best Mexican food I've ever had. I will say though I loved the enchiladas and if I came back here that would probably be my go to order.

We didn't order any drinks but they do have a bar you can sit at if this is your thing.

If I'm ever in the area again I'll definitely be stopping by.

address: 70 University Ave, Toronto, ON M5J 2M4, Canada

analyzed_reviews.review: We ordered the chicken & ribs, and the chipotle chicken. The rack of ribs was very dry and was not worth it. The flavour was lacking as well. But we will say the chicken in both dishes was really tasty and juicy. Ut basically carried the dish. We were a bit surprised that shrimps and ribs were all made on the same grill. We requested to ensure no shellfish contamination was made because of allergy reasons but they weren’t able to do so. Our allergy was not severe so we still ended up taking the risk and got the ribs. The soup and fries were decent. But the main star was the dessert. The white chocolate brownie was amazing and it made us want to give an extra star just for it. The place was very lively and it was hard to get the waiter’s attention, which was kinda overwhelming at times. But he gave the dessert on the house since we were celebrating a special day, which was really nice!
